result.formatted_address: 4 Pine St, Tai Kok Tsui, Hong Kong
result.name: Roti King Indian Fusion Cuisine

reviews.text: Good Indian food. Little expensive. But nice staff

Food tasted amazing! Portions were generous. Expect to smell like curry after you eat there - we had to wash our clothes to get the smell out as it remained overnight even after hanging. Maybe better to get it to go but if you don't mind smelling like curry, definitely a good place for Indian food.
Astoundingly good value and the food is excellent

Rude owner (chef). 
He really doesn’t care about tourists and will not treat you well, you will not fill comfortable as he has fixed local customers. He will continuously warn you for little things like tissue paper etc...

Food wise it is ok but over priced.

Food is really delicious but the place is lacking proper ventilation.. Literally makes your eyes teary while waiting for your food if you happened to order the house's specialty. We ordered lamb curry and chicken massala and my fav. mango lassi(yummy!) however our eyes stings all through out our time in there, food is really great though and got a reasonable price. And oh one more thing, you better place an order to go rather than dine in or you'll end up having food perfume lol, which is pretty uncomfortable if you will ride a public transpo 😂  like we did... anyways it's a delicious smell, i guess …
